INSERT INTO `recipe_instructions` VALUES (2924,1171,1,'Cook the pasta according to the package directions. Meanwhile, heat the olive oil in a skillet over medium heat.'),(2925,1171,2,'Add the walnuts and cook, stirring often, until lightly toasted and fragrant, about 4-5 minutes. Add the apples, parsley, salt, and pepper and toss to combine.'),(2926,1171,3,'Cook until apples are desired tenderness. Spoon apple mixture over pasta and sprinkle with the parmesan cheese. Serve immediately. Serves 4. Adapted from\nReal Simple Magazine.'),(2927,1172,1,'Combine the flour, 1 teaspoon of salt, baking powder, and next 7 ingredients in a pie plate'),(2928,1172,2,'stir until blended and smooth. Pour enough oil into a dutch oven or deep frying pan to generously cover the bottom of the pan. Heat on medium to medium high heat.'),(2929,1172,3,'Dip strips into the batter, coating well. Fry the eggplant 3 to 5 minutes on each side or until golden. Drain well on paper towels.'),(2930,1173,1,'Cook rice according to package directions. While the rice is cooking, drain beans reserving 2 tablespoons of the liquid. Combine beans, re'),(2931,1174,1,'Preheat oven to 450 degrees or grill to medium-high. If baking, place a sheet of foil on a cookie sheet.'),(2932,1174,2,'Center sweet potatoes, apples, and cranberries on the foil (see photo above). Sprinkle with brown sugar. Combine butter or margarine and cinnamon'),(2933,1174,3,'drizzle on top. Cover with another piece of aluminum foil and seal the sides to make one large foil packet, leaving room for heat to circulate inside.'),(2934,1174,4,'Bake 25 to 30 minutes in the oven or grill 20-25 minutes in covered grill until sweet potatoes are tender.'),(2935,1174,5,'Remove top of the packet carefully as there will be a lot of steam and yummy juice in the bottom. AFTER'),(2936,1175,1,'Preheat oven to 400 degrees. Cook pasta to al dente per package directions, drain and put in a large bowl. In a large skillet, heat 3 tablespoons olive oil over medium high heat.'),(2937,1175,2,'Add the corn, salt and pepper to taste, and cook until lightly golden, about 6-8 minutes. Add to the bowl with the pasta. In the same pan, put remaining 3 tablespoons olive oil'),(2938,1175,3,'add the zucchini, season with salt and pepper, and cook until tender and golden brown, about 6-8 minutes.'),(2939,1175,4,'(If you are short on time, microwave the zucchini for a few minutes on high before adding it to the pan.) Add to the bowl with corn and pasta.'),(2940,1175,5,'To the same skillet, on medium low, add the onion, 1 teaspoon salt and pepper to taste. Cook, stirring occasionally, until the onion is translucent, about 2-3 minutes.'),(2941,1175,6,'Add the tomatoes, garlic, oregano, and red pepper flakes and cook until the tomatoes soften and begin to form a sauce, about 5 minutes.'),(2942,1175,7,'Stir in the tomato paste and cook for 1 minute. Add the wine and cook until the wine is reduced and the sauce thickens, a few minutes more.'),(2943,1175,8,'Add the tomato sauce, basil, mozzarella and half the parmesan to the bowl with the vegetables and stir to combine.'),(2944,1175,9,'Transfer back to the pan if it’s oven safe or a 9×13 dish sprayed with cooking spray. Sprinkle with remaining parmesan and bake until golden brown on top, 20-25 minutes.'),(2945,1176,1,'Combine the dry ingredients (first 6) in a large bowl, stirring well. In another bowl, combine the zucchini and remaining 5 ingredients, stirring well.'),(2946,1176,2,'Add to flour mixture, stirring just until dry ingredients are moistened. Spoon batter into 2 greased and floured loaf pans (I use Baker’s Joy).'),(2947,1176,3,'Bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour or until a toothpick inserted in the center comes to clean. Cool in pans on a wire rack for 10 minutes'),(2948,1176,4,'remove from pans and cool completely or serve warm. Also freezes well and is perfect for a snack or breakfast on the road.\nAdapted from\nThe Ultimate Southern Living Cookbook, 1999'),(2949,1177,1,'Place asparagus and onion in a large pot with\n1 cup\nvegetable broth. Bring broth to a boil, reduce heat, cover, and simmer until vegetables are tender (about 20 minutes).'),(2950,1178,1,'Combine salad greens, mandarin oranges, and strawberries. Toss with balsamic vinaigrette until well coated. Sprinkle with pecans and blue cheese. Serve and enjoy.'),(2951,1178,2,'Sweet-and-Spicy Pecans\n1/4  cup sugar\n1  cup warm water\n1  cup pecan halves\n2  tablespoons sugar\n1  tablespoon chili powder\n1/8  teaspoon ground red pepper\nStir together 1/4 cup sugar and water until the sugar dissolves.'),(2952,1178,3,'Add pecans and soak for 10 minutes ONLY. Drain, discarding sugar water. Combine 2 tablespoons sugar and the remaining ingredients in a Ziploc bag. Add pecans and shake to coat.'),(2953,1178,4,'Bake pecans on a lightly greased baking sheet at 350 degrees for 10 minutes. Let cool. Adapted from\nSouthern Living All-New Favorite Five-Star Recipe Collection, 2001'),(2954,1179,1,'Combine all ingredients until well blended. Refrigerate for at least an hour if possible. Can be doubled or halved and serves lots!'),(2955,1180,1,'Combine first 4 ingredients in a large bowl.\nCombine eggs, milk, and oil'),(2956,1180,2,'and to flour mixture, stirring with a wire whisk until dry ingredients are moistened.\nCook in a preheated, OILED waffle iron until golden.'),(2957,1181,1,'Cook pasta according to the package directions. While pasta is cooking, heat the oil in a large nonstick skillet over medium-high heat.'),(2958,1181,2,'Add the chicken and sprinkle with salt and pepper. Cook and stir until chicken is thoroughly cooked and the juices run clear. Remove chicken from the pan.'),(2959,1181,3,'Whisk together the wine, chicken broth, mustard, and cornstarch. Add to pan, stir and bring to a boil. Cook for 1 minute.'),(2960,1181,4,'Stir in olives and artichokes (trim tough ends if needed) and cook for another minute. Add chicken and drained, cooked pasta to the pan. Cook until warm.'),(2961,1181,5,'Sprinkle with parsley and serve immediately. Adapted from\nCooking Light Annual Recipes, 2004'),(2962,1182,1,'Preheat oven to 325 degrees. Grease an 8×8 inch glass baking dish. In a small saucepan, heat milk to simmering over medium-high heat.'),(2963,1182,2,'(If you are short on time, chop the chocolate now. It will melt quicker!)\nMeanwhile, in a 3 quart saucepan, melt chocolates over low heat. Remove from heat'),(2964,1182,3,'with a fork or wire whisk, stir in sugar, vanilla, and salt, then eggs until combined. Slowly whisk simmering milk into melted chocolate mixture until blended.'),(2965,1182,4,'Gently stir in bread. Let stand 20 minutes to allow bread to absorb milk mixture, stirring once. Pour bread mixture into baking dish. Cover with foil and bake pudding 40 minutes.'),(2966,1182,5,'Uncover and bake 15 minutes longer or until knife inserted in center of pudding come out almost clean. Cool on a wire rack.'),(2967,1183,1,'Add 4 teaspoons oil to skillet'),(2968,1183,2,'add tofu in a single layer and cook until golden brown on both sides, approximately 5-7 minutes, flipping halfway through.'),(2969,1183,3,'Transfer to paper towels to soak up any excess oil and then slice into strips. This usually takes 3 batches.'),(2970,1183,4,'During the last batch, cook rice noodles according to package directions for pasta'),(2971,1183,5,'drain. Add 1 1/2 teaspoons oil, carrots, garlic, and scallion whites to skillet. Cook until softened, about 5 minutes. Add lime juice mixture and bring to a simmer.'),(2972,1183,6,'Add noodles, and cook, stirring gently until warm and well combined. Add tofu and eggs and toss to combine. Salt to taste.'),(2973,1184,1,'Place trimmed chicken thighs in a gallon sized ziploc bag. Combine remaining ingredients and stir well. Pour mixture over chicken and seal the bag.'),(2974,1184,2,'Put the bag in a bowl so that all of the chicken is covered with the marinade. Refrigerate for 8 hours, turning occasionally. Drain chicken thighs, reserving marinade.'),(2975,1184,3,'Grill chicken thighs over medium coals 8 minutes on each side or until done, basting frequently with soy sauce mixture.'),(2976,1185,1,'Cook bacon in a large skillet until crisp'),(2977,1185,2,'remove bacon, crumble, and set aside. In the same pan, cook the onion and garlic until tender (add a little olive oil or butter if the onion is sticking to the pan)'),(2978,1185,3,'DRAIN. Combine bacon, onion mixture, and all the remaining ingredients in a large bowl. Spoon into a lightly greased  2  1/2 quart bean pot or baking dish.'),(2979,1185,4,'Cover and bake at 375 degrees for 1 hour or until beans are tender. Make sure to check the garbanzo beans for doneness, they tend to need some extra time.'),(2980,1185,5,'Serves lots and is fabulous leftover as well. Adapted from\nThe Ultimate Southern Living Cookbook, 1999'),(2981,1186,1,'Cook pasta according to package directions.'),(2982,1187,1,'Cook pasta according to package directions, drain, and place in a large serving bowl. In a small skillet, heat 1/4 cup of the olive oil over medium heat.'),(2983,1187,2,'Add the garlic and pine nuts. Cook for 2-3 minutes or until nuts begin to turn golden but not brown. Add this mixture to the pasta.'),(2984,1187,3,'Add tomatoes, spinach, and herbs to the pasta, stirring gently to combine. For the dressing, combine lemon juice, salt, and pepper.'),(2985,1187,4,'Gradually add the remaining 1/4 cup olive oil and whisk until smooth and well combined. Pour dressing over salad and toss gently to combine.'),(2986,1187,5,'Serve immediately or chill until ready to serve.'),(2987,1188,1,'Preheat oven to 425 degrees. In a large bowl, toss all the cut vegetables with the olive oil, salt, and pepper. Spread in a single layer on 2 cookie sheets.'),(2988,1188,2,'Bake for 25-35 minutes, turning once, until all vegetables are at the desired tenderness. Sprinkle with parsley if desired and serve immediately.'),(2989,1188,3,'Adapted from\nBarefoot Contessa Family Style, 2002.'),(2990,1189,1,'Preheat oven to 375 degrees. Fit piecrust into a 9-inch pie-plate. Cook fresh vegetables in microwave on high for 5-6 minutes or until crisp-tender.'),(2991,1189,2,'Spoon into prepared crust, and top with cheeses. Combine egg yolks and remaining 4 ingredients, stirring well. Pour over cheese. Bake for 40-45 minutes or until set.'),(2992,1189,3,'Let stand 10 minutes before serving. Serves 6. (Adapted from\nThe Ultimate Southern Living Cookbook, 1999)'),(2993,1190,1,'Preheat oven to 375 degrees. Lightly butter 6 standard muffin cups. With a rolling pin, flatten each bread slice and cut in half diagonally.'),(2994,1190,2,'Press the bread halves into the muffin cups, making a large well in the center and making sure that the bread comes up to the edge of the cup. Brush bread with remaining butter.'),(2995,1190,3,'Place 1 bacon slice in each bread cup and carefully crack an egg over each. Season with salt and pepper to taste. Bake for 20-25 minutes or until egg whites are just set.'),(2996,1190,4,'Sprinkle cheese on for the last few minutes of baking. Serve immediately. Adapted from\nEveryday Food, September 2010.'),(2997,1191,1,'Preheat oven to 400 degrees. Lightly spray an 8×8 pan with cooking spray. If using fresh spinach, cook in olive oil over medium-high heat until wilted.'),(2998,1191,2,'Transfer to a colander and press out as much liquid as possible. Layer bread cubes, then spinach and cheese, in pan. In a medium bowl, whisk together eggs, milk, salt and pepper.'),(2999,1191,3,'Pour over bread and spinach (don’t worry if all the cheese ends up on top). Bake for 35 minutes.'),(3000,1192,1,'Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Cut the squash in half crosswise and remove the seeds. Next, cut a THIN slice from the bottom of each squash so that they will sit flat.'),(3001,1192,2,'Place squash halves, cut side up, in a 9×13-inch baking dish. Add an inch of hot water to the pan with the squash.'),(3002,1192,3,'Combine apple and next 3 ingredients and spoon evenly into the squash halves. Cover with aluminum foil and bake for 1 hour or until squash is tender. Sprinkle with pecans.'),(3003,1193,1,'Cook the chicken breasts in melted butter until browned, no longer pink, and juices run clear. Remove from pan and keep warm.'),(3004,1193,2,'To make the glaze: In the same pan, put equal amounts of honey and lime juice.'),(3005,1193,3,'Cook over medium heat stirring constantly until thickened and bubbly (see photo below), season with dill. Coat chicken pieces with glaze and serve immediately.'),(3006,1194,1,'Heat oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat. Add green onions and sauté 5 minutes or until tender. Add spinach and sauté 2 more minutes.\nCombine eggs, milk, and remaining ingredients in a bowl'),(3007,1194,2,'stir well with a whisk. Stir in spinach and onion mixture. Pour filling into crust. Bake at 350 degrees for 35 minutes (40 minutes if you prefer a firmer texture).'),(3008,1195,1,'Add potatoes, salt, pepper, and 1 cup of the cheese. Cook until heated, but do not boil.'),(3009,1196,1,'Preheat the oven to 400 degrees. Combine the black beans and next 4 ingredients in a saucepan over medium low heat. Allow to simmer for 5 minutes.'),(3010,1196,2,'To assemble the tortillas: Place a tortilla on a plate and add 2 heaping tablespoons of the bean mixture to the middle. Layer with the green onions, salsa, and cheddar cheese.'),(3011,1196,3,'Roll the tortilla up and place it in a lightly sprayed 9×13 pan.'),(3012,1196,4,'Repeat until you have used up all the tortillas (I sometimes use the larger size tortillas if that’s what I have on hand).'),(3013,1196,5,'There is usually bean mixture left and it is delicious dipped with tortilla chips. Bake about 15 minutes or until lightly browned.'),(3014,1196,6,'Top with sour cream, additional green onions, salsa, or cheese and enjoy! Adapted from\nThe Six O’Clock Scramble\n, Aviva Goldfarb, 2006'),(3015,1197,1,'Place strawberries in container of a blender or food processor'),(3016,1197,2,'cover, and process until smooth. Transfer puree to a large bowl. Add half-and-half, sour cream, powdered sugar, and balsamic vinegar'),(3017,1197,3,'stir with a wire whisk until smooth. Cover and chill at least 2 hours.'),(3018,1198,1,'Cook fettuccine according to package directions, drain, and set aside. Cook broccoli in microwave on high for 5 minutes or until desired tenderness. Melt butter in a large skillet.'),(3019,1198,2,'Stir in broccoli and cook 1 minute or until thoroughly heated. Add whipping cream, salt, and pepper'),(3020,1198,3,'cook until warm. Add fettuccine, then parmesan cheese, tossing gently.'),(3021,1199,1,'Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Combine the first 8 ingredients in a large bowl and mix well. Shape into 2 loaves measuring about 7 1/2 x 4 inches.'),(3022,1199,2,'Place on a lightly greased rack in broiler pan. Bake for 40 minutes. Combine 1/2 cup ketchup, brown sugar, and mustard'),(3023,1199,3,'spoon over the meatloaf and bake an additional 15 minutes or until meat thermometer registers 160 degrees. Makes 2 loaves or 8 servings.\nAdapted from\n“The Ultimate Southern Living Cookbook”\n, 1999'),(3024,1200,1,'Cook the onion (celery and pepper also, if desired) and ground turkey in a large sauté pan over medium heat, stirring occasionally for 10 minutes or until the turkey is thoroughly cooked.'),(3025,1201,1,'Add whipped cream and fresh raspberries. Finish with another cup of whipped cream.'),(3026,1202,1,'Combine the first 5 ingredients in a salad bowl and toss gently. If you have time, cover and chill. Combine oil and remaining dressing ingredients in a jar.'),(3027,1202,2,'Cover tightly, shake vigorously and drizzle over the salad just before serving. Salad serves 4, dressing will be enough for at least 2 salads.'),(3028,1202,3,'Adapted from\nSouthern Living’s Five-Star Recipe Collection, 1990'),(3029,1203,1,'Combine first 7 ingredients in a serving bowl. Cook pasta according to package directions'),(3030,1203,2,'drain. Add tomato basil sauce to pasta and toss well. Add additional salt and pepper to taste. Sprinkle with cheese if desired. Serve warm or chilled.'),(3031,1203,3,'Sauce can be made up to a day in advance. Chill until ready to use. Adapted from\nThe Ultimate Southern Living Cookbook, 1999\nSave\nSave'),(3032,1204,1,'Place potatoes and water in a 2-quart casserole dish and cover. Microwave on HIGH 12-15 minutes, stirring half way, until desired tenderness. Let stand 5 minutes, drain.'),(3033,1204,2,'Microwave butter until melted. Add salt, pepper, and parsley. Pour over potatoes and toss to coat. Serve immediately.'),(3034,1205,1,'Preheat oven at 375 degrees.'),(3035,1205,2,'Combine Flour, Baking Powder and Salt in a bowl\nSeparately in a Larger Bowl, Cream Butter Substitute, Sugar, Egg, Almond Milk and Vanilla\nAdd Dry Ingredients into Larger Bowl in thirds - mixing well each time.'),(3036,1205,3,'Kneed into a ball - cut in half and wrap in parchment - cool in refrigerator for at least 30 minutes\nRoll out and use cookie cutters. Place on non-stick cookie sheets.'),(3037,1205,4,'Bake (375 degrees) for 9-11 minutes. Decorate with Icing.'),(3038,1206,1,'Preheat oven to 275 degrees - place foil-lined pan in oven to also preheat.'),(3039,1206,2,'Mix together in a bowl (hands work best):  Salmon, Eggs, Chopped Green and Red Peppers, Crushed Crackers, and Salt & Pepper to taste.'),(3040,1206,3,'Pat out salmon patties or burgers - no more than 3/4\" thick. In a non-stick pan, add 1 Tbs of Olive Oil - brown salmon patties on both sides.'),(3041,1206,4,'After browning, place in pre-heated pan, cover with foil and bake for 15 minutes to ensure thorough cooking of egg ingredient.'),(3042,1207,1,'Heat 1 Tbs oil in a 6+ quart Dutch oven or soup pot over medium-high heat. Add chopped sausage then saute until\nbrowned. Transfer to a plate then set aside.'),(3043,1207,2,'Lightly season both sides of chicken thighs\nwith Cajun Seasoning then place skin side down in dutch oven or pot.'),(3044,1207,3,'Sear on both sides\nuntil golden brown, 3-4 minutes a side (does not need to be cooked through,) then transfer to\nplate with sausage and set aside.'),(3045,1207,4,'Remove pot from heat for a few minutes to cool slightly then place back over medium\nheat.'),(3046,1207,5,'Add remaining 2 Tbs oil then sprinkle in flour and whisk constantly until mixture is\nthe color of caramel, this is your roux.)  It gets quite gooey.'),(3047,1207,6,'Add bell pepper, celery, garlic and onion then saute until vegetables are slightly tender - do not overcook - scraping the bottom of the pot to make sure roux doesn\'t burn.'),(3048,1207,7,'Add tomatoes - pulling them apart and crushing them with your hands as you add them. Pour in the rest of the tomato sauce from the can.'),(3049,1207,8,'Stir in chicken broth and continue to scrape the bottom of the pot. Pull apart chicken into small pieces and add to the pot. Also add back the chopped sausage.'),(3050,1207,9,'Add 1 Tbs of Cajun Seasoning, 1/4 tsp paprika, 2 bay leaves and 1/4 tsp cayenne pepper (or more if you like it hot).'),(3051,1207,10,'Turn heat up to bring gumbo to a low boil, then turn heat down to medium-low and simmer uncovered for\n1-1/2 hours.'),(3052,1207,11,'Add raw shrimp and turn up heat to Medium High for 3-5 minutes until the shrimp are pink. Optional:  Sprinkle with Filing Powder and stir in after the shrimp is cooked.'),(3053,1207,12,'Remove Bay Leaves before serving. Serve over or under cooked white rice'),(3054,1208,1,'Add Chili Mix ingredients except for the \"Masa\" (Flour)\nFor the Carroll Shelby\'s Chili Kit - I typically use about half the salt packet, and about 2/3\'s the packet of cayenne pepper.'),(3055,1208,2,'Suit yourself on taste. I definitely use the entire (large) packet of the Chili Seasoning.'),(3056,1208,3,'Add:  Chopped/Shredded Stewed Tomatoes, Tomato Sauce and Water\nCook on low (or medium low) for about 30 minutes, stirring occasionally\nAdd Light and Dark Kidney Beans, lower temp to simmer.'),(3057,1208,4,'Simmer for about 30-45 minutes until the kidney bean casing becomes firm but not popped open. Add about 1 tablespoon of flour (\"Masa\") - simmer for another 5 minutes.'),(3058,1208,5,'Top off with tortilla chips (gluten free) or Saltine Crackers. Sorry - no cheese or sour cream toppings! I know, this is hard to give up.'),(3059,1209,1,'Preheat oven to 325 degrees F. In a medium saute pan, over medium-low heat, cook the onions, olive oil, salt, pepper, and optional thyme until translucent.'),(3060,1209,2,'Add the Worcestershire sauce, chicken stock, tomato paste (and optional fresh parsley) .... and mix well. Set aside and allow to cool.'),(3061,1209,3,'Combine the ground turkey, bread crumbs, eggs, and onion mixture in a large bowl. Mix well and shape into a loaf on an ungreased sheet pan. Spread the ketchup evenly on top.'),(3062,1209,4,'Bake for 1 hour until the internal temperature is 160 degrees F. and the meatloaf is cooked through. Allow to rest before slicing.'),(3063,1209,5,'Hint:  A pan of hot water in the oven under the meatloaf will keep the the meatloaf moist'),(3064,1210,1,'Cook Time\n5\nminutes\nmins\nCool Time\n1\nhour\nhr\nTotal Time\n1\nhour\nhr\n10\nminutes\nmins\nCourse\nBreakfast, Dessert\nCuisine\nAmerican, Indian\nServings\n6'),(3065,1212,1,'Add Kellogg’s Rice Krispies cereal. Stir until well coated. Using a buttered spatula or wax paper, evenly press the mixture into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan coated with cooking spray.'),(3066,1212,2,'Cool. Cut into 2-inch squares. Best if'),(3067,1213,1,'Preheat the oven to 350 F. Mix the dry ingredients together and set aside. In a separate large bowl, cream the softened butter and sugars until light and fluffy.'),(3068,1213,2,'Add the eggs one at a time. In a separate bowl, mash the bananas and stir in the milk and vanilla.'),(3069,1213,3,'Gradually add the flour mixture and banana mixture to the butter mixture, alternating between the two. Mix until just combined. Gently fold the blueberries into the batter.'),(3070,1213,4,'Pour the batter into a paper-lined muffin tin. Bake for about 20 minutes. Photo Credit: Sage Scott. Jere Cassidy\n\n\n\n\n\nGreat muffins.'),(3071,1213,5,'I just picked fresh blueberries and had bananas, so this was the perfect recipe to use up all the fruit. Tastes great and the recipe was super easy.'),(3072,1213,6,'Jane\n\n\n\n\n\nThese muffins are amazing! I made them last night and they were gone within an hour. My husband loved them so much that he ate two in one sitting.'),(3073,1213,7,'Lisa\n\n\n\n\n\nThese muffins had a wonderful taste and texture. I froze half for later and can’t wait to enjoy them again.'),(3074,1213,8,'How to Store Leftover Muffins\nIf you don’t devour all of these scrumptious banana blueberry muffins in one sitting, they’ll stay fresh at room temperature for up to three to four days.'),(3075,1213,9,'To keep them in tip-top shape, store them in an airtight container. But if that’s not an option, a big ol’ Ziploc bag with a layer of paper towels will do the trick.'),(3076,1213,10,'The towels will soak up any sneaky moisture and stop your muffins from going soggy. Just swap out the paper towels daily to maintain peak tastiness. Photo Credit: Sage Scott.'),(3077,1214,1,'Place all ingredients\nexcept\nthe cream cheese and half-and-half in a Crock-Pot or\nslow cooker\n. Cover and cook on high for 3-4 hours or low for 7-8 hours.'),(3078,1214,2,'Remove and shred the chicken. Return the chicken to the pot and add the cream cheese and half-and-half.'),(3079,1214,3,'Cover and cook on high for about 15 minutes or until the cream cheese is melted and the chili is slightly thickened.'),(3080,1215,1,'Cook Time\n0\nminutes\nmins\nTotal Time\n2\nminutes\nmins\nCourse\nSnack\nCuisine\nAmerican\nServings\n4'),(3081,1216,1,'Add Ins\nAlthough I tend to stick to the basics with my granola and add fresh fruit when I’m ready to eat it, you can mix  a cup of dried fruit or\nmini chocolate chips\ninto the cooled granola to zhuzh it up a bit.'),(3082,1216,2,'Great options include dried cranberries, dried blueberries, and raisins. Important'),(3083,1217,1,'Cook What You Love\nEasy Shirazi Salad\nA fresh, crunchy, and refreshing salad of cucumbers, tomatoes, bell peppers, and a tangy dressing is the perfect side for BBQ chicken!'),(3084,1217,2,'Get the Recipe\n20\nPlant Based Folk\nEasy Orange and Fennel Salad\nThis refreshing salad pairs peppery arugula with segmented oranges, slivered almonds, and slices of fennel to create the perfect summer side dish.'),(3085,1217,3,'Get the Recipe\n21\nWhat a Girl Eats\nTomato Salad\nFor a vegan, Whole 30, and paleo-friendly side salad, try this recipe featuring heirloom cherry tomatoes and fresh mint.'),(3086,1217,4,'Get the Recipe\n22\nEnd of the Fork\nItalian Butter Bean Salad\nWhether you call them\nbutter beans\nor lima beans, the savory flavors of this refreshing Italian-style salad are a delicious accompaniment to BBQ chicken.'),(3087,1217,5,'Get the Recipe\n23\nKibitz Spot\nEasy Potato Salad\nBy making the classic recipe gluten free and dairy free, this fast and easy potato salad is an allergy-friendly BBQ chicken side dish – and it even has a vegan option.'),(3088,1217,6,'Get the Recipe\n24\nFlavor the Moments\nClassic Coleslaw Recipe\nCrisp and crunchy shredded cabbage topped with a creamy coleslaw dressing is a classic BBQ chicken side dish.'),(3089,1217,7,'Get the Recipe\n25\nGypsy Plate\nHawaiian Macaroni Salad\nTransform your backyard BBQ into a tropical paradise with this\nluau-inspired\nBBQ chicken side dish. Get the Recipe\n26\nNourish'),(3090,1218,1,'Cook Time\n50\nminutes\nmins\nTotal Time\n1\nhour\nhr\n5\nminutes\nmins\nCourse\nSide Dish\nCuisine\nAmerican\nServings\n10'),(3091,1219,1,', pour into greased\nmini\nmuffin tins, and bake. Yes, it’s really that easy! Sage Advice:\nNotice that the word “mini” is in bold italics above.'),(3092,1219,2,'It’s absolutely essential that you use a mini muffin tin to create these bite-sized Brazilian treats. They will not work in a regular muffin tin.'),(3093,1220,1,'Mix dry ingredients. Whisk wet ingredients. Combine and fold in diced peaches. Whip cream cheese with powdered sugar and swirl it into the top.'),(3094,1220,2,'Top with more peaches and bake until golden and set. Cool slightly, then dig in. Photo Credit: Sage Scott.'),(3095,1221,1,'Add the flavors of Italy to your grilled chicken with this cold pasta salad.'),(3096,1221,2,'Your favorite pasta\nis tossed with sweet cherry tomatoes, peppers, olives, and mozzarella, then seasoned with a sweet, tangy dressing that’s irresistibly good.'),(3097,1221,3,'Get the Recipe\n18\nFit Mama Real Food\nEasy Broccoli Salad\nGo green with this broccoli salad that’s not just another leafy side.'),(3098,1221,4,'It’s a crunchy medley of raw broccoli, sunflower seeds,\npumpkin seeds\n, and dried cranberries, all brought together by a tangy dressing of avocado oil mayonnaise, lemon juice, and\nmaple syrup\n.'),(3099,1221,5,'Get the Recipe\n19\nBegin with Balance\nFruit Salsa\nAdd a sweet and tangy twist to your grilled chicken with this Fruit Salsa. A medley of mango,'),(3100,1222,1,'Cook Eat Live Love\nDairy Free Mashed Potatoes\nThese creamy, fluffy mashed potatoes skip the butter and milk to deliver a delicious dairy-free dish.'),(3101,1222,2,'They’re ready to star alongside any hearty chicken dinner in under 30 minutes, using simple ingredients like olive oil and garlic to layer in extra flavor.'),(3102,1222,3,'Get the Recipe\n3\nCorrie Cooks\nDairy Free Potato Salad\nThe Instant Pot simplifies a classic dish, using a pressure cooker to perfectly cook potatoes and hard-boiled eggs in just minutes.'),(3103,1222,4,'Packed with flavor from fresh dill and a duo of mustards, this creamy potato salad is a crowd-pleasing side for fried chicken that stands out at a potluck.'),(3104,1222,5,'Get the Recipe\n4\nSunglow Kitchen\nSweet Potato Salad\nTry this sweet potato beet salad for a hearty side dish that’s colorful and packed with fresh flavors.'),(3105,1222,6,'Roast sweet potatoes and beets, toss them with walnuts and feta, and drizzle them with honey balsamic dressing.'),(3106,1222,7,'It’s a feast of fall colors for the eyes and a perfect match for fried chicken.'),(3107,1222,8,'Get the Recipe\n5\nThree Olives Branch\nMacaroni Salad\nThis classic, homemade macaroni salad blends simple, traditional flavors into a perfect side dish for fried chicken.'),(3108,1222,9,'Featuring a mix of eggs, celery, onion, and a tangy mayo-based dressing, this versatile side pairs wonderfully with any chicken dish.'),(3109,1222,10,'Get the Recipe\n6\nJoyfully Mad\nGrilled Squash\nBalance the decadence of crispy fried chicken with this quick and healthy grilled Squash.'),(3110,1222,11,'Ready in just 15 minutes, it features simple ingredients like yellow summer squash, olive oil, salt, and pepper.'),(3111,1222,12,'Get the Recipe\n7\nA Little and a Lot\nJicama Salad with Apples\nThis refreshing jicama salad is tossed with crisp apples, radishes, and a tangy honey lime dressing.'),(3112,1222,13,'Its vibrant flavors and delightful crunch make it a delicious dish to complement fried chicken.'),(3113,1222,14,'Get the Recipe\n8\nSourdough Brandon\nSourdough Buttermilk Biscuits\nThese flaky and fluffy biscuits deliver a delicious twist on a Southern staple.'),(3114,1222,15,'Ready in under 30 minutes, they are made with sourdough discard, making them a smart and tasty way to use leftover starter.'),(3115,1222,16,'Get the Recipe\n9\nWhat’s Smoking\nSmoked Corn-on-the-Cob\nInstead of making roasted sweet corn to accompany your fried chicken, try this smoked corn-on-the-cob recipe.'),(3116,1222,17,'It’s easy to make and delivers deliciously seasoned corn that’s perfectly smoked, making it a standout side dish.'),(3117,1222,18,'Get the Recipe\n10\nClassic Coleslaw\nThis classic coleslaw is easy to whip up using basic ingredients like green cabbage, red cabbage, carrot, and a tangy dressing.'),(3118,1222,19,'Make it ahead of time for a creamy, crunchy side dish for fried chicken that’s dairy-free.'),(3119,1222,20,'Get the Recipe\n11\nChristina’s Cucina\nSpicy Coleslaw\nFor a tantalizing twist on a classic, try this spicy slaw that’s borderline addictive.'),(3120,1222,21,'It combines shredded cabbage and carrots with a dressing spiced up with green pepper Tabasco, a splash of vinegar, and a bit of mayo.'),(3121,1222,22,'This easy-to-make side adds a kick to any meal and is perfect for those who like their fried chicken paired with a bit of heat.'),(3122,1222,23,'Get the Recipe\n12\nThe Short Order Cook\nAir Fryer Green Beans\nThese crispy air fryer green beans are a quick and healthy fresh vegetable side dish that’s ready in just 10 minutes.'),(3123,1222,24,'Toss fresh green beans with avocado oil and a special blend of seasonings, air fry to perfection, and then finish with a squeeze of fresh lemon.'),(3124,1222,25,'Get the Recipe\n13\nLara Clevenger\nEasy Blackstone Broccoli\nThis broccoli recipe is perfect for a quick and healthy side dish.'),(3125,1222,26,'After seasoning the broccoli, grill it on your Blackstone Griddle to achieve a delightful charred yet tender finish.'),(3126,1222,27,'It\'s a versatile dish that complements fried chicken and just about any other'),(3127,1223,1,'Stir in spices, quinoa, tomato sauce, and some cheese. Fill each pepper half with the prepared mixture. Top with more cheese and bake until hot and golden.'),(3128,1223,2,'You can find step-by-step instructions in the recipe card below.'),(3129,1224,1,'Place the peach halves on a plate, cut side up, and sprinkle the fruit with a little salt. Put one scoop of cheese in the center of each peach, about 1 ½ teaspoons per peach half.'),(3130,1224,2,'Top each peach with a basil leaf, either whole or cut lengthwise into strips. Drizzle honey over the peach halves, and serve immediately.'),(3131,1225,1,'Cook the onion, carrots, and celery until softened. Stir in the garlic. Add the Chicken and Broth.'),(3132,1225,2,'Place the chicken on top of the veggies, then add the seasonings, low-sodium chicken broth, and water. Pressure Cook. Secure the lid and cook on high pressure for 10 minutes.'),(3133,1225,3,'Let the pressure naturally release for 10 minutes, then carefully turn the valve to release any remaining steam. Shred the Chicken.'),(3134,1225,4,'Remove the chicken and shred it into bite-sized pieces. Cook the Noodles. Bring the broth to a simmer, and add the egg noodles. Cook until tender. Stir and'),(3135,1226,1,'Heat olive oil in a saucepan and cook the onion and jalapeno until softened. Add the Spices. Stir in the garlic, cumin, oregano, smoked paprika, salt, and pepper.'),(3136,1226,2,'Cook a little longer. Stir in the Chiles. Mix in the canned green chiles, ensuring that they are well combined with the seasonings. Simmer.'),(3137,1226,3,'Pour in the chicken or vegetable broth and let it simmer, uncovered, for about 10–12 minutes. Blend Until Smooth.'),(3138,1226,4,'Use an immersion blender\n, countertop blender, or food processor to create a silky consistency. Or, leave it chunky if you prefer. Finish with Lime Juice.'),(3139,1226,5,'Stir in fresh lime juice, and adjust seasoning to taste. Photo Credit: Sage Scott.'),(3140,1227,1,'Add the remaining cherries to a high-powered blender and puree. Add the coconut milk, sugar, agave, and salt to the blender. Blend until smooth.'),(3141,1227,2,'Pour the blended ice cream mixture into an airtight container and chill for at least 2 hours.'),(3142,1227,3,'To Churn in an Ice Cream Machine\nOnce the creamy amaretto ice cream base has chilled, churn according to your ice cream machine’s instructions.'),(3143,1227,4,'If your ice cream maker has a mix-in opening (like my Cuisinart), add the soaked cherries and chocolate chips once the dessert starts to thicken (usually with about 5 minutes to go).'),(3144,1227,5,'If your ice cream maker does not allow you to blend in additional ingredients, gently fold them in by hand after churning.'),(3145,1227,6,'When the ice cream is done in the churn, it will resemble soft'),(3146,1228,1,'Cook the shallots in olive oil for 1–2 minutes, then add the mushrooms and cook for an additional 5 minutes. Stir in garlic and cook for another minute.'),(3147,1228,2,'Season with salt and pepper to taste. Fry the eggs. In a separate pan, cook the eggs in olive oil over medium-low heat.'),(3148,1228,3,'Cover and cook until the whites are set but the yolks are runny. Toast the bread. Get it golden and crisp. Assemble.'),(3149,1228,4,'Spread Boursin on the toast, pile on the mushroom mixture, top with an egg, and finish with parsley.'),(3150,1229,1,'Preheat the oven to 350°F and lightly grease two standard 6-cavity donut pans (or a muffin tin if you’re freestyling). Make the Buttermilk.'),(3151,1229,2,'Combine the milk and apple cider vinegar, then set aside to curdle slightly while you prepare the other ingredients. Mix the Donut Batter.'),(3152,1229,3,'Whisk together the dry ingredients, cream the wet ingredients, and then stir them together just until combined. Fill the Pans.'),(3153,1229,4,'Pipe or spoon the batter into the prepared pans, filling each cavity about two-thirds full. Bake.'),(3154,1229,5,'Bake for 10–12 minutes, or until a toothpick inserted into the center comes out clean. Cool in the pan for 5 minutes before transferring to a wire rack. Make the Topping.'),(3155,1229,6,'While the donuts cool slightly, whisk together sugar and cinnamon. In a separate bowl, mix the melted butter with a small amount of re'),(3156,1230,1,'Mix the meatball ingredients\nScoop and shape the meatballs\nBroil to perfection\nPhoto Credit: Canva.'),(3157,1230,2,'How to Make Dairy-Free Italian Meatballs\nUse this ingredient list for a dairy-free version of these tasty meatballs.'),(3158,1230,3,'Then, follow the same instructional steps in the regular recipe below. 1 lb ground chicken\n1 lb chicken sausage\n1 cup Italian-style panko bread crumbs\n½ cup grated\nvegan\ncheese\nOR'),(3159,1231,1,'Mix ½ cup\npowdered sugar\nand 1 teaspoon lemon zest into a small bowl.'),(3160,1231,2,'Slowly stir 2 to 3 teaspoons of freshly squeezed lemon juice into the powdered sugar, one teaspoon at a time, until you reach the desired consistency.'),(3161,1231,3,'Move the lemon glaze to a small plastic zipper bag, snip off a small piece of the corner, then drizzle the glaze over the cooked and fully cooled muffins. Photo Credit: Sage Scott.'),(3162,1231,4,'How to Make Raspberry Muffins\nThese raspberry muffins are fast and easy to make:\nPreheat the oven to 375 F. Mix the dry ingredients together and set aside.'),(3163,1231,5,'Combine the wet ingredients. The mixture will be pale yellow. Slowly add the wet ingredients to the flour mixture, stirring until just combined. Gently fold in the raspberries.'),(3164,1231,6,'Spoon the muffin batter evenly into the cups of a lined muffin tin. Top with turbinado sugar or streusel, if desired (see'),(3165,1232,1,'Bake plain portobello mushroom caps for a few minutes. Saute the spinach in olive oil with minced garlic. Add the cream cheese.'),(3166,1232,2,'Stuff the mushroom caps with the filling and top with the panko breadcrumb mixture. Bake until the breadcrumbs are golden brown. And voila!'),(3167,1232,3,'Your spinach stuffed portobello mushrooms are ready to be devoured.'),(3168,1233,1,'Add taco meat to a base of shredded or chopped greens, then top with your favorite ingredients and drizzle with\navocado crema\nand a dash of hot sauce. Nachos.'),(3169,1233,2,'Top tortilla chips with taco meat, black beans, and your favorite shredded cheese. Bake or air fry until the cheese melts, then garnish with fresh top'),(3170,1234,1,'Add the granulated sugar and cornstarch (if you’re using it) to your chosen appliance (high-powered blender, food processor, or coffee grinder).'),(3171,1234,2,'For every cup of granulated sugar, add one tablespoon of cornstarch. Blend until the sugar is very fine and fluffy.'),(3172,1234,3,'If you’re using a powerful blender, this will take about 30 to 60 seconds. If you’re using a food processor or coffee grinder, this will take about 4 minutes.'),(3173,1234,4,'Stir the sugar to ensure it’s been thoroughly blended. If it feels gritty when you rub it between your fingers, continue blending until it reaches a powdery consistency.'),(3174,1234,5,'Powdered sugar made at home can be stored indefinitely. To maintain its freshness, keep it in an airtight container in a cool, dry place. If you plan on'),(3175,1235,1,': Place the lobster mixture in an airtight container and refrigerate for up to three days.'),(3176,1235,2,'Realistically, it might not last that long—leftovers in my house tend to disappear with a fork straight out of the container within 24 hours.'),(3177,1235,3,'Get creative with leftovers\n: The lobster mixture is delicious on its own or as a topping for a bed of lettuce, turning it into a quick and easy lobster salad.'),(3178,1236,1,'Heat things up. Warm the olive oil in a large skillet over medium heat.'),(3179,1236,2,'Add the ground chicken and diced onion, then cook until the chicken is browned and the onions are soft and translucent, about 3 to 5 minutes. Drain off any excess'),(3180,1237,1,'Pour huckleberry vodka over ice and top with your favorite ginger beer. Stir gently and garnish with a lime wedge and fresh huckleberries or blueberries.'),(3181,1238,1,'Place all of the ingredients in a food processor or blender. Blend on high until the avocado crema is smooth and creamy, scraping down the sides as needed.'),(3182,1238,2,'Transfer the crema to a squeeze bottle or bowl and'),(3183,1239,1,'Cook the onion in olive oil until soft, then stir in garlic. Make the Filling. Add green chiles and shredded chicken, then remove from heat. Assemble the Casserole.'),(3184,1239,2,'Layer enchilada sauce, tortillas, chicken mixture, and cheese in a greased baking dish. Repeat layers. Add the Sauce. Pour the remaining enchilada sauce over the top. Bake.'),(3185,1239,3,'Cover with foil and bake at 350°F for 30 minutes. Uncover, add cheese, and bake for 10 more minutes.'),(3186,1240,1,'Whisk together\nthe egg yolks, sugar, and salt, then stir in the cream and milk. Cook the custard\nover medium heat until it is thick enough to coat the back of a wooden spoon.'),(3187,1240,2,'Stir in flavor\nwith vanilla, bourbon, cinnamon, and the roasted peaches. Chill, churn (or no-churn),\nand freeze until scoopable.'),(3188,1240,3,'Homemade Peach Ice Cream without a Machine\nDon’t have an\nice cream maker\n? Don’t worry!'),(3189,1240,4,'You can still enjoy dairy-free homemade peach ice cream with just a little extra patience and a sturdy spoon.'),(3190,1240,5,'The texture won’t be quite as airy as churned, but it’s still incredibly creamy and delicious. Pour\nthe chilled custard base into a shallow'),(3191,1241,1,', mix them into a'),(3192,1242,1,'Add the peaches, yogurt, milk, honey or maple syrup, cinnamon, cardamom, and a pinch of salt. Blend until smooth. Taste and adjust the sweetness if needed. Chill or'),(3193,1243,1,'Cook Time\n45\nminutes\nmins\nTotal Time\n1\nhour\nhr\n55\nminutes\nmins\nCourse\nDessert, Snack\nCuisine\nAmerican\nServings\n9'),(3194,1244,1,'Add the liquid (either a combination of broth and wine or just broth)\nSteam the mussels\nAdd the cream\nTop with fresh parsley\nEnjoy! Photo Credit: Canva.'),(3195,1244,2,'Why Soak Mussels in Flour Water? Although some cooks will say this step is not necessary for farm-raised mussels, I always soak my mussels in flour water.'),(3196,1244,3,'Mussels are filter feeders, which means they constantly take in water and filter out any particles like plankton or algae as their food source.'),(3197,1244,4,'When you soak them in a mixture of cold water and flour, something magical happens.'),(3198,1244,5,'The mussels start filtering out the tiny particles of flour from the water just as they would with their natural food sources.'),(3199,1244,6,'This process not only helps clean out any remaining sand or grit inside the shells but also causes the mussels to expel some of their own juices while trying to get rid of those pesky flour particles, which ultimately results in plumper, more tender mussels once cooked.'),(3200,1244,7,'Side Dishes to'),(3201,1245,1,'Slice & Bake Sugar Cookies\nInspired by Pillsbury cookie dough logs, these vegan slice-and-bake sugar cookies blend the simplicity of shortbread with the sweetness of sugar cookies.'),(3202,1245,2,'With just five ingredients, this recipe is a breeze to make and easy to customize in terms of colors and flavors. The vegan sugar cookie dough can be prepped and stored in the'),(3203,1246,1,'Blend your chosen fresh berries or frozen fruit with plain, unsweetened yogurt, the sweetener of your choice, and any'),(3204,1247,1,'Bake and cool the muffins. Mix up the glaze and drizzle it over the cooled muffins.'),(3205,1247,2,'How to Store Strawberry Cream Cheese Muffins\nBecause this strawberry muffin recipe uses cream cheese in the filling and milk in the glaze, I recommend'),(3206,1248,1,'Cook Time\n40\nminutes\nmins\nCourse\nMain Course\nCuisine\nItalian\nServings\n4'),(3207,1249,1,'Whisk all sauce ingredients (except the cornstarch slurry) in a saucepan over medium heat. Simmer 3–4 minutes, until the sugar dissolves. Thicken it.'),(3208,1249,2,'Add the cornstarch slurry while whisking. Simmer another 3–5 minutes until slightly thickened. Remove from heat. Cook the shrimp.'),(3209,1249,3,'Sauté shrimp in olive oil until pink and cooked through, about 2–3 minutes per side. Season with salt and pepper. Toss and');
